			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-lg-8 col-md-8">
					<div class="tab-contents">
						<p class="contents-active">At present, distributed applications are established relying on Ethereum and IPFS which causes slow response due to the lack of information retrieving. However, Lambda resolves the issue elegantly with structural data and fast read and writing ability provided by sharding and partition strategies.
<br/>Nowadays, with the boost of distributed applications, the Lambda decentralized structural cloud storage plan can be applied to both information source tools and telecommunications tools, and pan-entertainment services since it can provide more reliable, faster, and securer storage plans.</p>
						<p>n the existing blockchain storage plans, there are plans of storage in the blockchains, point-to-point file system, and distributed cloud storage, however, each of them has defects. The storage in blockchains results in slow transactions and large size of memory on a single point; point-to-point file system requires users to be online all the time; distributed cloud storage supports static files only, which are unable to be updated or accessed by programs.<br/>To solve the issues mentioned above, Lambda is transformed to keep online permanently, write and read fast, and support various types such as Rich Media.</p>
						<p>In the artificial intelligence field, the value of data turns out to be increasingly important. Nevertheless, the exchange value feature of the blockchain is tailored for data exchange, during which the data owner adopts smart contracts to sell primitive data, and then sell analysis results, forming a closed loop. <br/>Based on time sequence and data exchange, Lambda is able to incubate a better ecosystem in the artificial intelligence sector. </p>
						<p>IoT is featured with considerable size of memory, time sequence, and fast update, which appeals to Lambda, the storage solution based on blockchain technologies with time stamp function and high extensibility. <br/>No matter in IoT or IoE scenarios, the cost-effective storage plan of Lambda can not only avoid energy consumption caused by cloud computing but also better meet storage requirements of time sequence compared with network edge computing. </p>
