					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-lg-8 col-md-8">
					<div class="tab-contents">
						<p class="contents-active" style="opacity:0.8">Lambda is a homogeneous multi-chain design, of which the MainChain provides registration, global ledger management, and transaction liquidation for sub-chains, immensely expanding Lambda ecology based on the capabilities of multiple WorkChains responsible for accessing different services. <br>Moreover, Lambda supports transactions and telecommunications across the chains, therefore, achieving authorization, record, and request transfer of data requests, statistics of data responses and consensus management of database nodes, and data completeness verification.  </p>
						<p>With the Sharding technology, Lambda WorkChains utilizes real-time loading schedules flexible Sharding and combined Sharding to ensure the capability of handling a million RPS requests. <br> Adopting the sub-chain model, Lambda performs sharding automatically according to accounts or request content to guarantee high concurrence, and meanwhile ensures the completeness and security of data through the cross verification mechanism with the MainChain. </p>
						<p>Lambda follows the increment expansion principle to establish the dynamic Sharding mechanism, making it possible to distribute loads to storage nodes at equilibrium and ensure consistency at the same time. <br> It also supports cluster and partition, which can be used to solve network congestion. The partition based on geographical positions and operators also adopts the inquiry, node addition and deletion, and conflict resolving strategies applied in sharding, which can guarantee the balance of loads and consistency of data. </p>
						<p>Based on the ABE algorithm, Lambda establishes an efficient data access control plan for mobile cloud storage using online-offline and outsourcing decoding technologies. <br> Based on the BLS-PDP and MF-PDP algorithms, Lambda fulfills the completeness verification of data to ensure the eternal security and privacy of data. <br>Based on the CCHDP algorithm, Lambda enables a storage mechanism in which a group of nodes can be sharded dynamically. </p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
